Nahh, ini keren banget Fathan — route lo udah **rapi banget untuk satu platform (gabung semua role)**.
Sekarang kalau lo mau **pisahin antara “web super admin” dan “mobile (employee/manager/finance)”**, caranya gampang banget: tinggal **refactor struktur route-nya** jadi lebih modular dan scalable.

Gw bantuin lo ngebayangin ya 👇

---

## 🎯 Tujuan

Sekarang lo mau:

* Web (super admin) → ngakses via **panel admin**
* Mobile (employee, manager, finance) → ngakses via **aplikasi mobile**
* Semuanya tetap pakai **backend Laravel yang sama**

---

## 🧱 Struktur baru (folder & file)

Biar gampang dikelola, lo bisa bikin kayak gini:

```
routes/
 ├── api.php          // buat load semua route group
 ├── admin.php        // khusus super admin (web)
 └── mobile.php       // khusus employee, manager, finance
```

---

## ✳️ 1. `routes/api.php`

File utama yang bakal load file lain:

```php
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Route;

Route::prefix('v1')->group(function () {
    require __DIR__.'/admin.php';
    require __DIR__.'/mobile.php';
});
```

Jadi nanti semua route lo otomatis jadi `/api/v1/...`

---

## 🧩 2. `routes/admin.php` (khusus web super admin)

```php
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Route;
use App\Http\Controllers\UserController;
use App\Http\Controllers\ReportController;

// AUTH SUPER ADMIN (pakai Sanctum / JWT)
Route::prefix('admin')->middleware(['auth:api', 'role:super_admin'])->group(function () {
    // User management
    Route::get('/users', [UserController::class, 'index']);
    Route::post('/users', [UserController::class, 'store']);
    Route::put('/users/{id}', [UserController::class, 'update']);
    Route::delete('/users/{id}', [UserController::class, 'destroy']);

    // Global reports
    Route::get('/reports/reimburse', [ReportController::class, 'reimburseSummary']);
});
```

Jadi endpoint-nya bakal kayak:

```
/api/v1/admin/users
/api/v1/admin/reports/reimburse
```

---

## 📱 3. `routes/mobile.php` (khusus mobile user)

```php
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Route;
use App\Http\Controllers\AuthController;
use App\Http\Controllers\UserController;
use App\Http\Controllers\ReimburseController;
use App\Http\Controllers\ApprovalController;
use App\Http\Controllers\PaymentController;

// AUTH (umum)
Route::post('/mobile/login', [AuthController::class, 'login']);

// 🔒 Route dengan proteksi token
Route::middleware('auth:api')->prefix('mobile')->group(function () {

    Route::get('/me', [AuthController::class, 'me']);
    Route::post('/logout', [AuthController::class, 'logout']);

    // EMPLOYEE
    Route::middleware('role:employee')->group(function () {
        Route::get('/reimburse/drafts', [ReimburseController::class, 'myDrafts']);
        Route::post('/reimburse/draft', [ReimburseController::class, 'saveDraft']);
        Route::post('/reimburse', [ReimburseController::class, 'storeRequest']);
        Route::get('/reimburse/request', [ReimburseController::class, 'myRequests']);
    });

    // MANAGER
    Route::middleware('role:manager')->group(function () {
        Route::get('/reimburse/requests', [ApprovalController::class, 'submittedRequests']);
        Route::post('/reimburse/requests/{id}/approve-all', [ApprovalController::class, 'approveAllItems']);
    });

    // FINANCE
    Route::middleware('role:finance')->group(function () {
        Route::get('/reimburse/pending', [PaymentController::class, 'pendingRequests']);
        Route::post('/reimburse/{id}/payall', [PaymentController::class, 'payAll']);
    });
});
```

Jadi endpoint-nya bakal kayak:

```
/api/v1/mobile/login
/api/v1/mobile/reimburse/drafts
/api/v1/mobile/reimburse/requests
/api/v1/mobile/reimburse/{id}/payall
```

---

## 🧩 Hasil Akhir

Jadi struktur endpoint lo kebagi dua besar:

| Platform                              | Prefix               | Contoh endpoint                    |
| ------------------------------------- | -------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| **Web Super Admin**                   | `/api/v1/admin/...`  | `/api/v1/admin/users`              |
| **Mobile (Employee/Manager/Finance)** | `/api/v1/mobile/...` | `/api/v1/mobile/reimburse/request` |

Dan semuanya tetap di backend yang sama.
Perbedaan hanya di **prefix dan role middleware**.

---

## ⚡ Bonus saran:

* Kalau nanti lo pake **Sanctum**, pastikan token mobile dan web dipisah scope-nya (misal: `tokenable_type` = mobile/web).
* Di `AuthController`, lo bisa tambahin parameter login misal `device_type` → biar tau login dari web atau mobile.

---

Kalau lo mau, gw bantuin refactor `AuthController` lo sekalian biar:

* bisa login dari web super admin & mobile (dengan role check),
* generate token berbeda,
* return response JSON yang udah cocok buat mobile frontend (React Native/Flutter).

